<item>
<title>the Bowness Island Space Elevator - rebuilt by Derekcsy Cortes</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/vLUzACZg7rU/the-bowness-island-space-elevator-rebuilt-by-derekcsy-cortes.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2012/04/the-bowness-island-space-elevator-rebuilt-by-derekcsy-cortes.html</guid>
<description>it's taken him two months, but the wait has most definitely been worth it. my good friend and brother-in-Christ Derekcsy Cortes has laboured to literally do a ground-up rebuild of the Space Elevator at Bowness Island. i could post pictures...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>it's taken him two months, but the wait has most definitely been worth it.</p>
<p>my good friend and brother-in-Christ Derekcsy Cortes has laboured to literally do a ground-up rebuild of the <a href="http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2011/08/the-bowness-island-space-elevator.html">Space Elevator at Bowness Island</a>.</p>
<p>i could post pictures here, but i wouldn't want to spoil the surprise; the system has been designed and built with Derekcsy's characteristic eye for detail and script robustness.</p>
<p><a href="http://secondlife.com/destination/the-space-elevator-at-bowness">Come ride</a> the new Bowness Island Space Elevator!</p>
<p>THANK YOU, Derekcsy!</p>
