<item>
<title>recording of Matthew Ong's presentation at ICTLT 2012 on the citizenship education game The Rise of Li' Ttledot</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/cV48i0EtDtA/recording-of-matthew-ongs-presentation-at-ictlt-2012-on-the-citizenship-education-game-the-rise-of-li-ttledot.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2012/04/recording-of-matthew-ongs-presentation-at-ictlt-2012-on-the-citizenship-education-game-the-rise-of-li-ttledot.html</guid>
<description>the one-hundred-and-ninety-fifth episode of ventriloquy is a recording of a presentation by my friend and colleague Matthew Ong on the citizenship education videogame The Rise of Li' Ttledot, at the recent International Conference on Teaching and Learning with Technology (ICTLT)...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>the <a href="http://voyager.blogs.com/podcasts/01Apr12Ventriloquy195.m4a">one-hundred-and-ninety-fifth episode</a> of ventriloquy is a recording of a presentation by my friend and colleague Matthew Ong on the citizenship education videogame <i>The Rise of Li' Ttledot</i>, at the recent International Conference on Teaching and Learning with Technology (ICTLT) 2012 conference.</p>
<p>Li' Ttledot was conceptualized by Matthew and his former colleagues at the Anglo-Chinese School (Junior).</p>
<p>we enacted it in a Primary Five class last year. the 16.2 MB download is chaptered and is sync-ed with the presentation slides.</p>
<p><img src="http://voyager.blogs.com/images/littledot.png" /></p>
