<title>Minecraft and map literacy</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/_ObrD7z05_A/minecraft-and-map-literacy.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2012/03/minecraft-and-map-literacy.html</guid>
<description>Teacher: "what can we find on a map?" Students: "coordinates" T: "very good, what are coordinates?" S: "x, y, z" T: "did you learn that in primary school?" S: "No! we learnt it in Minecraft!"</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Teacher: "what can we find on a map?"</p>
<p>Students: "coordinates"</p>
<p>T: "very good, what are coordinates?"</p>
<p>S: "x, y, z"</p>
<p>T: "did you learn that in primary school?"</p>
<p>S: "No! we learnt it in Minecraft!"</p>
