<item>
<title>i remember… (the Singapore Airlines Boeing 747 and me)</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/Asdb03rEO3U/i-remember-the-singapore-airlines-boeing-747-and-me.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2012/02/i-remember-the-singapore-airlines-boeing-747-and-me.html</guid>
<description>i remember … my first view of the Swiss Alps, when i was fourteen years' old, from the Upper Deck of a Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-200 'Super-B' i remember … staring up at you from the Parade Square at Pulau...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>i remember …</p>
<p>my first view of the Swiss Alps, when i was fourteen years' old, from the Upper Deck of a Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-200 'Super-B'</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>staring up at you from the Parade Square at Pulau Tekong as you flew overhead, wondering what adventures you'd bring your passengers to today</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>leaving to study in England, when i was eighteen years' old, taxing towards the runway at Changi Airport with the Commodores playing on the rubberized earphones, in a Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-300 'Big Top'</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>being awoken in the middle of the night by the clunks and whirrs as we began final approach into Bahrain</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>catching my first glimpse of the Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-400 'Megatop' parked on the tarmac, through the window of a 7-series, as we drove towards the Welcoming Ceremony</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>coming home with my undergraduate degree, preparing to resume National Service, flying nonstop from London to Singapore on a Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-400 'Megatop'</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>how i cried when i learned about SQ006</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>posting to my blog from 38000 feet somewhere over the Caspian Sea, from a Singapore Airlines Boeing 747-400 'Megatop'</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>that you winged me across the Atlantic for my postgraduate studies in Boston, and you winged me safely back.</p>
<p>i remember …</p>
<p>how you've always been A Great Way To Fly</p>
<p>i will remember you always.</p>
<p><img src="http://voyager.blogs.com/images/9vspm.JPG" /></p>
