<title>the Christmas truce</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/kEd3roJOVXs/the-christmas-truce.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2011/12/the-christmas-truce.html</guid>
<description>for this year's Christmas episode, i invite us to pause and consider one of the names of the Christchild, namely, the Prince of Peace. 2011 has been a turbulent and unpredictable year, and this Christmas it is my prayer that...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>for this year's <a href="http://voyager.blogs.com/podcasts/25Dec11Ventriloquy194.m4a">Christmas episode</a>, i invite us to pause and consider one of the names of the Christchild, namely, the Prince of Peace.</p>
<p>2011 has been a turbulent and unpredictable year, and this Christmas it is my prayer that the Peace and Joy that only Jesus can bring, will fill the hearts of you and your loved ones.</p>
<p>do join me in this 3.2 MB download, with the scripture passage taken from Isaiah 9: 6. it's a familiar passage, but one that bears prayerful contemplation.</p>
<p>for to us a child is born, to us a son is given, and the government will be on his shoulders, and he will be called Wonderful Counsellor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.</p>
