<item>
<title>colliding realities, part 2</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Voyeurism/~3/X00VpW18UL4/colliding-realities-part-2.html</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2011/10/colliding-realities-part-2.html</guid>
<description>as a curious follow-up to my post from earlier today, i had the strangest sense of colliding realities when i visited the RMS Titanic exhibition at the ArtScience Museum this morning. when i walked through the painstaking recreations of the...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>as a curious follow-up to my <a href="http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2011/10/the-atomic-world-has-a-mini-map.html">post from earlier today</a>, i had the strangest sense of colliding realities when i visited the <a href="http://blogs.wsj.com/searealtime/2011/10/31/titanic-show-steams-into-singapore/">RMS Titanic exhibition</a> at the <a href="http://www.marinabaysands.com/Singapore-Attractions/ArtScience-Museum/">ArtScience Museum</a> this morning.</p>
<p>when i walked through the painstaking recreations of the first-class cabins, the Grand Staircase and the Promenade Deck, i honestly was telling myself - "but i've been here before!"</p>
<p>and indeed i had - because for the past four years i have been walking her decks, as well as did my part to <a href="http://voyager.blogs.com/voyeurism/2007/10/take-her-to-sea.html">work with my great friend Reborn Wingtips</a> to bring her back to life :-)</p>
<p><img src="http://voyager.blogs.com/images/secondlife/titanic.jpg" /></p>
